  "unit": {
    "verdict": "ok",
    "note": "Present perfect vs past simple (revision): present perfect (have/has + past participle) for experience / unfinished time / present result with already/yet/just/ever/never/since/for/so far; past simple for finished/specific past with yesterday/ago/last/in 1990; the time-expression contrast (present perfect NEVER with a finished-time word; past simple NEVER with since/for). 31 vocab + 58 grammar, full v1 parity (floor 40 → 58). 4 verify lenses clean after fixes (translation 0 defects). The grammar agent hit a transient API error mid-run but had already written its 58 items, so the whole unit went through the full validate fix-loop: relabeled 3 group-sorts off German category text ('(2./3. Form)' / 'for + Spanne' / 'since + Anfangspunkt' → form-exemplars 'visited'/'have visited' and the keywords 'for'/'since'); reworded gf.005 'Verneinung/Gegenwartsbezug' + gs.004 'Verbformen'→'Wörter'; flipped tr.004 to deToEn (it was enToDe with a German instruction prompt → direction/lang conflict; now German-present-+-seit → English present perfect); disambiguated cp.001 (→Anna) and cp.002 (sie mid-sentence); fixed mt.001 (was ambiguous — both present-perfect stems accepted both since/for endings, 4 valid bijections — reworked to TENSE + content/pronoun-locked pairs so each matches uniquely); fixed gf.016's non-standard sentence-final 'just' (moved the blank to 'I have ___ looked at the collection'); tr.008 contraction tier→full; granted the past participles / irregular pasts / contraction fragments ('s/'ve) + cognates (officer/painting/murderer/club/moments). Validate green."
